      "risk": "Team lacks event sourcing experience, leading to incorrect aggregate design, missing events, or broken projections",
      "severity": "high",
      "mitigation": "Invest in training. Start with a spike/proof-of-concept on a single loan workflow. Establish clear event design guidelines and review process. Consider bringing in a consultant for the initial design phase."
    },
    {
      "risk": "Event schema evolution becomes unmanageable over time as regulatory requirements change",
      "severity": "high",
      "mitigation": "Adopt an explicit event versioning strategy from day one (e.g., upcasters that transform v1 events to v2 at read time). Use an event registry/catalog. Never modify stored events — only add new versions."
    },
    {
      "risk": "Eventual consistency between write and read models causes user confusion or race conditions in the UI",
      "severity": "medium",
      "mitigation": "Implement read-your-own-writes consistency for the originating user (e.g., return the command result with the new state, or poll the read model until the expected version appears). Set clear SLAs for projection lag."
    },
