      "severity": "medium",
      "mitigation": "Implement snapshotting. Monitor aggregate load times. Set a threshold (e.g., snapshot every 50 events). Most loan applications have a bounded lifecycle, limiting event count naturally."
    },
    {
      "risk": "Projection rebuild time grows unbounded as event volume increases over years",
      "severity": "medium",
      "mitigation": "Partition event store by time or aggregate type. Implement incremental projection rebuilds with checkpointing. Archive old event streams that are past regulatory retention requirements."
    }
  ],

